1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: A young Celia faces the first of many obstacles and decides to participate in a music contest.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: Without her father's permission, Celia attends a party with the intention of seeing her musical idols.

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: Celia dances the night away with Pedro unaware that her father suffered a heart attack after having caught them.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: After her father's rejection, Celia wants to give up on her dream of being a singer. She cannot stop blaming herself for what happened with her father.

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: Rogelio Martínez, the director of the Sonora Matancera, wants to hear Celia sing and she cannot contain her excitement.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: Taking advantage of Myrta's departure from the orchestra, Pedro encourages Celia to take her place.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: The singer of the Sonora Matancera invites Celia to sing one of her most famous songs and encourages her to follow her dream.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: Celia gets carried away by her feelings while giving Pedro a massage, unaware that Alberto is spying on them through the window.

9.title: Episode #1.9
9.plot: In one of his clandestine encounters with a woman, Pedro cannot get Celia out of his head.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: Celia can no longer stand the curiosity of knowing what Pedro feels about her and, with help of a song, declares her love for him on the train en route to Havana.

11.title: Episode #1.11
11.plot: After confronting Pedro on the train, Celia is confused and considering giving up on her dream of being a singer.

12.title: Episode #1.12
12.plot: Pedro pays Celia an unexpected visit and confesses that he is madly in love with her.

13.title: Episode #1.13
13.plot: After so many obstacles, Celia accomplishes winning the Radio Progreso singing contest in Havana.

14.title: Episode #1.14
14.plot: Simón Cruz is embarrassed of Celia and reproaches her for having sung without his consent.

15.title: Episode #1.15
15.plot: Simón is enraged to find out that Celia has a romance with the Sonora trumpeter, Pedro Knight, and decides to confront him.

16.title: Episode #1.16
16.plot: Celia auditions with the director of the Sonora Matancera and discovers that Pedro Knight is the band's trumpeter.

17.title: Episode #1.17
17.plot: After having achieved singing and dancing in front of the director Rogelio and the orchestra, Celia manages being approved as the new singer of the Sonora.

18.title: Episode #1.18
18.plot: Celia searches for Pedro to tell him that if he leaves the Sonora Matancera, then she will give up on her dream of being the singer of the orchestra.

19.title: Episode #1.19
19.plot: Celia finally signs a contract with the Sonora and she is welcomed on her first day of rehearsal.

20.title: Episode #1.20
20.plot: The band director gives Pedro Knight one last chance to remain a part of the Sonora Matancera.

21.title: Episode #1.21
21.plot: At the request of the Tropicana audience, Celia sings and for the first time dedicates a song to Pedro Knight.

22.title: Episode #1.22
22.plot: Celia is very well received in Mexico where her first tour begins as the singer of the Sonora.

23.title: Episode #1.23

24.title: Episode #1.24
24.plot: Pedro is madly in love with Celia and asks her to be his girlfriend without telling her the whole truth.

25.title: Episode #1.25
25.plot: After so many lies, Pedro confesses the truth about his personal life to Celia.

26.title: Episode #1.26
26.plot: Celia is going through ordeals in her career and in her personal life, but Pedro is always there to encourage her to keep fighting.

27.title: Episode #1.27
27.plot: Myrelys tries to provoke Celia by dedicating her performance to Pedro Knight.

28.title: Episode #1.28
28.plot: Celia is recognized globally as the best singer of the time and is winning important awards in her career.

29.title: Episode #1.29
29.plot: Pedro is choking on the feelings he has towards Celia and he tells her that her happiness is his happiness.

30.title: Episode #1.30
30.plot: After learning about Ollita's state of health, Celia is distraught and wants to do everything to make her mother get well.

imdb.plot outline: She dared to challenge the status quo in a time where salsa music was only a white-male territory. For the first time, the details of an amazing life will be told through a powerful drama that will have you glued to your seat. This Fall, get to know the woman who became the queen of salsa. Tune in to Telemundo for "CELIA", the story of Celia Cruz. Azúcar!
imdb.title: Celia
plot: She dared to challenge the status quo in a time where salsa music was only a white-male territory. For the first time, the details of an amazing life will be told through a powerful drama that will have you glued to your seat. This Fall, get to know the woman who became the queen of salsa. Tune in to Telemundo for "CELIA", the story of _Celia_ (qv) Cruz. Azúcar!::Del Rio

"_Celia_ (qv)" tells the story of one of the legends of Latin music with a major international career: _Celia_ (qv) Cruz. We will get to know the beginnings of her passion for singing in Cuba in the 1950s and of her recognition as the most determined singer of the popular group La Sonora Matancera. After leaving the island alongside her husband Pedro Knight, her artistic career conquered markets in other languages and she positioned herself as the most renowned singer in salsa music. She honored the genre and her beloved homeland, and she left an invaluable legacy that crowned her the Guarachera of the world.::LML
synopsis: "Celia" tells the story of one of the legends of Latin music with a major international career: Celia Cruz. We will get to know the beginnings of her passion for singing in Cuba in the 1950s and of her recognition as the most determined singer of the popular group La Sonora Matancera. After leaving the island alongside her husband Pedro Knight, her artistic career conquered markets in other languages and she positioned herself as the most renowned singer in salsa music. She honored the genre and her beloved homeland, and she left an invaluable legacy that crowned her the Guarachera of the world.
